‚Â¬Ãƒâ€¦Ã‚Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã†â€™ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…Â¡ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬Å¡Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â not tracked in git
.claude/
.claude/worktrees/
.claude/.workflow-state.json
# EXCEPT: hook scripts and shared workflow files must be tracked so
# isolated git worktrees inherit them. Without these negations, any
# `git worktree add` would lack post_format / post_write_prod_scan /
# stop_verify_gate, breaking parallel ralph-worker dispatch.
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/hooks/*.py
!.claude/hooks/tests/
!.claude/hooks/tests/**/*.py
!.claude/rules/
!.claude/rules/*.md
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/agents/*.md
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/skills/**/*.md
!.claude/docs/
!.claude/docs/*.md
!.claude/docs/knowledge/
!.claude/docs/knowledge/*.md
!.claude/prd.json
!.claude/workflow.json
CLAUDE.md
WORKFLOW.md
PROJECT_BRIEF.md
.mcp.json.example

